Sentencas: La0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (LSCO) films for use in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) have been deposited on yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ)(100) substrates by pulsed laser deposition (PLD).
Titulo: Pulsed laser deposition of conducting porous La-Sr-Co-O films

Sentencas: Both epitaxial and porous-polycrystalline films were fabricated.
Titulo: Pulsed laser deposition of conducting porous La-Sr-Co-O films

Sentencas: The porous films were formed by deposition at room temperature followed by anneal at from 450-750 degrees C to increase porosity.
Titulo: Pulsed laser deposition of conducting porous La-Sr-Co-O films

Sentencas: Resistivity measurements have shown that the porous LSCO films annealed at 550 degrees C yielded the lowest resistivity of 10(-2)
Titulo: Pulsed laser deposition of conducting porous La-Sr-Co-O films
Pulsed laser deposition of conducting porous La-Sr-Co-O films

Sentencas: The epitaxial LSCO films were deposited on YSZ(100) in the temperature range of 450 to 750 degrees C, and showed (110) preferred orientation.
Titulo: Pulsed laser deposition of conducting porous La-Sr-Co-O films

Sentencas: The electrical resistivity of the epitaxial LSCO films is 10(-3) Omega.cm for films deposited at 550 degrees C. (C) 1999
